definitions.definition: A thrust ; a push ; a sudden force that impels .
A wish or urge , particularly a sudden one prompting action .
examples: The impulse to learn drove me to study night and day.
When I saw the new book, I couldn't resist the impulse to browse through it.

definitions.definition: The integral of force over time .
examples: The total impulse from the impact will depend on the kinetic energy of the projectile.

main_definition: A thrust ; a push ; a sudden force that impels .
secondary_definitions: A wish or urge , particularly a sudden one prompting action .
